We have been working with @petcurean in their 2019 #UpliftTheUnderdog campaign to raise awareness of the many dogs in rescue shelters who often get overlooked for adoption because of age, health or behavior issues. Shelters were invited to nominate their most deserving dogs, and voting is now open to the public to help bring even more attention. Below is a list of all the nominees, and there are photos of some behind the first one. To learn more, cast your vote, and show support for these deserving dogs, please visit www.petcurean.com/underdog (link in bio!). The winner in each category will receive a 5-year supply of food from Petcurean, and each finalist is getting 1-year supply of food, a 500lbs food donation to their shelter and Petcurean will even pay for their adoption fee if they are adopted by the end of 2019. Voting is open from April 30 until May 6PST. The winner in each category will be announced on May 7 on @Petcurean’s account.
And if you’re able to consider adopting one of these loveable dogs, or know someone who might be interested, please spread the word!
